---
description: HTML UI rules for widget-side modals
globs: widget-src/ui/*.html
alwaysApply: false
---

## Messaging Contract

- Communicate with the widget using `window.parent.postMessage` with a `pluginMessage` payload, e.g.:
  ```js
  window.parent.postMessage(
    { pluginMessage: { type: 'add-tasks', text } },
    '*'
  );
  ```
- Keep message `type` values short and descriptive (`'add-tasks'`, `'export-close'`, etc.) and handle them in `ActionBar` / widget code.

## HTML & Assets

- Do not load external scripts or CSS from CDNs; keep HTML self-contained for reliability.
- Keep the UI simple: textarea/input for text, minimal buttons, lightweight inline styles or a small embedded stylesheet.
- Avoid heavy libraries; plain HTML/CSS/JS is preferred to keep bundle size and complexity low.

## UX Expectations

- The import UI should:
  - Clearly prompt the user to paste or type their list.
  - Send the final text when the user confirms (e.g. clicks "Add").
  - Close itself cleanly after sending a successful message.
- Any future modals (e.g. export view) should follow the same messaging pattern and stay focused on one task at a time.
